node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christoph Niemann on September 19, 2021. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Something that’s difficult to accept as an artist: we have no control over how, if and why people may like a piece of art.

While I work on a drawing, I have complete control: I can decide what to edit, delete or add. I can make it more obvious or more obscure, more serious or goofy.

But once I share the artwork publicly, i cede all the power to the audience. It may turn out that people love something that I only felt lukewarm about. Or that something I was extremely excited about falls flat. Sometimes people like something, but I feel they like it for the wrong reason (sounds absurd, but I’m sure fellow artists know the feeling).

It’s a rare and magic moment when it clicks between the art and a viewer. It doesn’t matter if the artist approves or understands why. 
I have to trust the audience to come to their own conclusions. More importantly, I have to trust the art to have a life and a will of its own.

OPEN STUDIO in Berlin this week
Tuesday Aug. 31 —Saturday Sep. 4
Hours:
Tuesday -Friday 4-7 PM
Saturday 11 AM - 6 PM
Schröderstrasse 2
10115 Berlin (Mitte)

We’re showing Linocuts from the new book and recent silk screen editions.
I will be around to chat around to sign/inscribe books.
Looking forward to seeing you!

Please remember to wear a mask and bring proof of testing, vaccination or recovery. 
PS: The linocuts will be available in the online shop as of today.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Christoph Niemann on August 15, 2021. May be an image of stripes.

node.text:
During the last lockdown, I rediscovered linocuts.
It’s a mess and I constantly cut myself, but I like that it’s very physical. As opposed to an ink drawing, where everything is about restraint, I really have to work against the medium - and each mark is final.
All these animal prints are in my new book “Zoo”
Each book is signed and comes with a letterpress print.
See link in bio or recent story for purchase link.

node.text:
"ZOO"
available only here: https://shop.christophniemann.com/products/zoo
122 pages, Hardcover, linen bound. Each book is signed and comes with an original letterpress print

I just published a new book with linocuts, drawings and collages :
"ZOO" by Christoph Niemann
See link in bio or recent story for more infor and purchase link

Hard cover book, linen, 122 pages, 31 x 24 cm (12.2 x 9.5 inches), 1st Edition 2021.
Each book is signed and comes with a print:
"Uhu", one color letterpress,
signed, 29,6 x 21 cm.

Published by @Abstractometer Press.
Design by the  incredible @arianespanier

During the second lockdown, I visited the two Berlin Zoos. The next three months I spent making linocuts, drawings, and collages.
This is what I came up with…
